                 <p className="text-lg text-neutral-600 font-light leading-relaxed">
                    Assuming a baseline where our current Digital Creative Share of Wallet is <strong className="text-red-600 font-bold">~20%</strong> (estimated to be Ogilvy's in TCCC), our path to <strong className="text-black font-medium">25% overall growth</strong> relies on systematic, conservative recapture across two main drivers:
                 </p>
              </div>

              <div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 max-w-5xl">
                  <div className="bg-white border border-neutral-200 p-6 rounded-xl flex items-start gap-4 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md hover:border-red-200 transition-all group cursor-default">
                      <div className="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-red-50 text-red-600 flex items-center justify-center font-bold shrink-0 group-hover:bg-red-600 group-hover:text-white transition-colors duration-300">1</div>
                      <div>
